FBIS4-14127 "drnes082dd_94010" FBIS-NES-94-082 Daily Report 26 Apr 1994 Palestinian Affairs 'Arafat Allegedly Offers Hamas Gaza Municipality 'Arafat Allegedly Offers Hamas Gaza Municipality JN2604124994 Amman SAWT AL-SHA'B in Arabic 26 Apr 94 pp 1, 18 JN2604124994 Amman SAWT AL-SHA'B Arabic BFN [By Riyad Mansur] [Excerpts] What is taking place between Palestine President Yasir 'Arafat and the Islamic Resistance Movement, Hamas? This question is being posed in light of the reported contacts between the two parties, especially after Hamas' pledge to Yasir 'Arafat to name him president if he voices commitment to implement Islamic law. Hamas' pledge seems to have been taken seriously by Yasir 'Arafat, who unhesitatingly held contacts with this movement's leaders in Gaza through Muslim Brotherhood leaders in Egypt to ask them to meet him in Cairo after his meeting with Israeli Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin. Hamas' pledge, however, was not taken seriously by the other Palestinian rejectionist factions that are allied with Hamas under the Alliance of Palestinian Forces. [passage omitted] The Palestinian president has prepared a complete file for the Cairo meeting. The file primarily addresses the situation in Gaza under the autonomy and spells out foundations for the relationship between the Hamas movement and the self-rule authority. SAWT AL-SHA'B has learned that 'Arafat will propose that Hamas take over the Gaza municipality in a preemptive attempt to prevent it from asking for half the seats of the self-rule. [passage omitted]
